<br>
Kuai knows what he is talking about (well... here at least.  heh).<br>
<br>
However, you aren't a warrior so it might not be as simple as &quot;put all points into sta.&quot;  The reason is that warriors get a greater use out of their stamina (i.e. more hp per point of sta) than other classes do.  Like my SK only gets something like 80% of the hp a warrior would get from the same about of stamina.  This is one reason why warriors have more hp than SKs.  I'm not sure what the hp/sta ratio is for rangers, but you can be sure that it is equal to or less than the SK one which means that sta helps, but isn't as vital as for a war.<br>
<br>
Also consider that you are not a tank (well, beyond about lvl 30-40 you aren't) so hp also isn't as vital for this reason.<br>
<br>
Personally I would say get agi and dex both to at least 75 and put the rest in str.  It'll help damage a little (very little) and help you not be encumbered (rangers are kinda weak).  I don't think sta is worth is <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> on a ranger</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->.  That having been said, I wouldn't both reroll.  All in agi isn't that bad. <p>-----------------------------------------------<br>
